summary: Why is a certain group of the fandom so obsessed with Daenerys? Even when they’re talking about Sansa, they some how find a way...
body:
Why is a certain group of the fandom so obsessed with Daenerys? Even when they’re talking about Sansa, they some how find a way to be petty and throw hateful jabs towards dany. So far I haven’t seen a single Dany fan say anything bad about Sansa but I’ve seen countless of her fans foam at the mouth to hate on Dany. Seriously why are y’all so bitter? It’s so ugly the way you guys act.

Anyways I can’t wait for BFF’s Daenerys Stormborn of House Targaryen and Sansa Stark of Winterfell to meet and braid each other’s hair!

summary: “Someone has to save our skins. Into the garbage chute, fly boy!” -Leia  “You belong where you are loved” -Emma Carstairs.  “All...
body:
“Someone has to save our skins. Into the garbage chute, fly boy!” -Leia

“You belong where you are loved” -Emma Carstairs.

“All Men Must Die. But we are not men.” -Daenerys Targaryen.

“I’m willing to fight for those who cannot fight for themselves.” -Wonder Woman.

“Friends don’t lie.” -Eleven.

“Even strength has to bow down to wisdom sometimes.” -Annabeth Chase.

“I do not stand by in the presence of evil.” -Alita.

I know this apply to anyone (and everyone should consider them), but I liked it when in the TV, movies or books, it was a badass woman (or girl) who delivered them to the audience. Enjoy.

caption:
asoiaf & got characters // pt. XXII - Fire and Blood (ver. I)

“Like their dragons the Targaryens answered to neither gods nor men. […] “Faster!” the ghosts cried as one, and she screamed and threw herself forward. A great knife of pain ripped down her back, and she felt her skin tear open and smelled the stench of burning blood and saw the shadow of wings. And Daenerys Targaryen flew.”
